"Thanks very much to the link to your MOWA recordings.  They are indeed breeding examples of the Eastern Regiolect and very different from my recordings from the Cape Breton region.  It does alter my interpretation of the distribution of the Nova Scotia regiolect to a smaller dialect west of Antigonish to the Cape Breton region and St. Paul’s Island, and expands the Eastern regiolect to western NS."
Dr. Jay Pitocchelli, Professor Emeritus

Biology Department
Saint Anselm College
Manchester, NH
